title: .net developer
description:
A .NET Developer is responsible for designing, coding, testing, and maintaining software applications using the .NET framework. They typically work with C#, ASP.NET, and other related technologies to develop scalable and efficient solutions. Responsibilities often include:

Software Development: Writing clean, scalable code using .NET programming languages.
Application Design: Designing and implementing software applications according to specifications.
Testing and Debugging: Testing and debugging applications to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
Maintenance and Support: Maintaining and upgrading existing systems as needed.
Documentation: Writing technical documentation for reference and reporting.
Collaboration: Working closely with other developers, UX/UI designers, and stakeholders.
Key skills include proficiency in C#, ASP.NET, MVC, SQL Server, and familiarity with front-end technologies like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
